Given an array of integers representing the daily temperatures, develop an algorithm to determine how many days you must wait until a warmer temperature arrives for each day. If no future day has a higher temperature, the waiting period for that day should be zero.

Example
Input: temperatures = [73, 74, 75, 71, 69, 72, 76, 73]
Output: [1, 1, 4, 2, 1, 1, 0, 0]
Explanation:

Day 1: Temperature = 73, wait 1 day for warmer temperature 74.
Day 2: Temperature = 74, wait 1 day for warmer temperature 75.
Day 3: Temperature = 75, wait 4 days for warmer temperature 76.
Day 4: Temperature = 71, wait 2 days for warmer temperature 72.
Day 5: Temperature = 69, wait 1 day for warmer temperature 72.
Day 6: Temperature = 72, wait 1 day for warmer temperature 76.
Day 7: Temperature = 76, no warmer future day, so 0.
Day 8: Temperature = 73, no warmer future day, so 0.
This problem requires an efficient solution to handle up to 100,000 temperatures, avoiding obvious but costly comparisons between all elements.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> dailyTemperatures(vector<int>& temperatures) {
        int n = temperatures.size();
        vector<int> answer(n, 0);
        stack<int> stk;

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
            while (!stk.empty() && temperatures[i] >= temperatures[stk.top()]) {
                stk.pop();
            }

            if (!stk.empty()) {
                answer[i] = stk.top() - i;
            }

            stk.push(i);
        }

        return answer;
    }
};
